THE time for trash talk is over for South Africa’s featherweight kingpins, Sydney “Skeleton” Maluleke and Lerato “Lights Out” Dlamini.The two warriors are ready for war after both comfortably making their seventh day compulsory weigh-in yesterday ahead of their World Boxing Council (WBC) bout at Emperors Palace in Ekurhuleni on Sunday.The Free State-born Dlamini and Maluleke, who hails from Malumulele in Limpopo, are scheduled to trade blows for the vacant WBC international featherweight (57,15kg) belt. if(typeof za24_DisplayAd != "undefined") za24_DisplayAd("300x250","2");var viewReq = new Array();function vu(u) {var i=new Image();i.src=u.replace("&amp;","&");viewReq.push(i);}vu("https://securepubads.g.doubleclick.net/pcs/view?xai\x3dAKAOjss_03UShS7IhDpDsr48w3gybj63q2vwybPFpnq5H5OmjDXDPcsa6tlXxNBvE7qmGU7oCk-OmOhyYyXBvXJK_IQ245nGL86xBkSeN93l2tggcm4Xa4p3rkzstVUOR_EkbWnxry-RSs-BMxb7pQrDV3y4hIQjqFNtNflZG3lAISe8RuIQcdv2qaX1IXQaxgzLt2LmE5oWa2KcS_vXh0KGx9udv1ztl0zS0KrwTwjxzoZIMTpdivYKTxdE2Wph1w5lwomFhlhE3GJuGhRav27i\x26sig\x3dCg0ArKJSzGpvzxtQnqxKEAE\x26urlfix\x3d1\x26adurl\x3d")

   
